Albert B. LOGAN, Trustee in Bankruptcy for the IDEAL BAKERY COMPANY, v. J. B. FOWLER. No. 1384. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. March 5, 1936. Albert B. Logan, of Colorado Springs, Colo., for appellant. J. A. Carruthers and Gerald W. Bennett, both of Colorado Springs, Colo., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on stipulation.
